Title: GUI Top
worldeditgui.generic.open.config.gui.com: The key open the in-game config GUI
worldeditgui.commands.set.comment:
Perform the //set
Sets all the blocks in the region
worldeditgui.commands.set.block.comment: The pattern of blocks to set
worldeditgui.commands.copy.comment:
Copy the selection to the clipboard.
Perform the //copy
worldeditgui.commands.past.comment:
Paste the clipboard’s contents
Perform the //past
worldeditgui.commands.move.comment:
Perform the //move
Move the contents of the selection.
worldeditgui.commands.move.number.commen: number of times to apply the offset.
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.comment:
Perform the //rotate
Rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Non-destructively rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Angles are provided in degrees and a positive angle will result in a clockwise rotation.
Multiple rotations can be stacked.
Interpolation is not performed so angles should be a multiple of 90 degrees.
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.number.comm: Amount to rotate on the y-axis
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.xyz.comment:
Perform the //rotate
Rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Non-destructively rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Angles are provided in degrees and a positive angle will result in a clockwise rotation.
Multiple rotations can be stacked.
Interpolation is not performed so angles should be a multiple of 90 degrees.
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.y.comment: Amount to rotate on the y-axis
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.x.comment: Amount to rotate on the x-axis
worldeditgui.commands.rotate.z.comment: Amount to rotate on the z-axis
worldeditgui.commands.stack.comment:
Perform the //stack
Repeat the contents of the selection.
worldeditgui.commands.stack.offset.comme: How far to move the contents each stack
worldeditgui.commands.stack.abers.commen: Used to specify different settings during block stacking operations.
worldeditgui.commands.flip.comment:
Perform the //Flip
Flip the contents of the clipboard across the origin.
worldeditgui.commands.flip.boolean.comme: When this switch is set to "false", the default direction will be used for the flip. When set to "true", the chosen direction will be used for the flip.
worldeditgui.commands.flip.offset.commen:
The direction to flip.
Requires the "Toggle Flip Direction" feature to be enabled.
worldeditgui.util.abers_5.s: [-s] Shift the selection to the last stacked copy
